model

Class MapConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.Observable
      • model.MapConfig

  • public class MapConfig
extends java.util.Observable
    Class that will hold map configurations and informations.. These configurations are related to the viewport visualization of the 2D map, so it contains informations like tile size and map size. It also relates to the cut size of tiles in the tileset since the size of the tile is set in this class As of version 0.5b, contains map camera configurations and mouse position point on map
    Since:
    0.1
    Author:
    Pedro Sampaio

      • createMap

        public Map createMap(java.lang.String[] layers,
                     java.util.ArrayList<Tileset> tilesets)
        Creates a map with the received layers and tilesets information and returns it. The layers information contains a string representing the tiles informations for each layer and each tileset contains the remaining informations needed to infer from what tileset the tile information is from Sets selected layer as 0 (first layer)
        Parameters:
        layers - the layers of the map to be created containing all tile informations for all layers
        tilesets - the tilesets of the map containing the remaining data necessary for the map creation
        Returns:
        the created map with the received information, or null if map creation could not be done correctly
        Since:
        1.5
